The paper deals with a variant of the Longest Common Subsequence problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses fixed-parameter algorithms and parameterized hardness results, which are topics commonly studied in computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem formulation involves strings and an alphabet, which suggests a possible connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the problem involves constraints on the subsequence, which could be related to graph theory (cs.GT).
